reviews.text: Best bubble tea here!try the summer drinks. You have many choices to choose!i've visited it many times,if you are a codarts student,you have discounts and that's awesome!

reviews.title: Rose Bubble Tea & Hong Kong Bubble Tea are good!
reviews.text: After had lunch, we went here for desserts. I ordered HongKong bubble tea, and my friend ordered Rose Bubble Tea. and I like her bubble tea more. but both taste good. I haven't see YoYo in Belgium, maybe they should have one in Kortrijk one!

additionalNames.name: Capelle aan den IJssel
additionalNames.long: Capelle aan den IJssel, The Netherlands

reviews.title: Super!
reviews.text: Super nice bubble tea with many choices. Place was pretty cozy as a hangout place. Our all-the-time favorite place to go!

reviews.title: Bubble tea
reviews.text: We had one of the best bubble teas ever there. Cool place. Try melon perfection from the selection of summer drinks. Great place to relax for a few minutes with the kids enjoying their drinks:)

reviews.title: Looked great, but didn't live up to expectations
reviews.text: This looked like a really hip place to try some bubble tea.  However it never seemed to match the cool atmosphere.  There were some annoyances such as not being able to use visa cards only mastercard, and some of the options I wanted were't available.  The bubble tea itself was nice, but not great.  Somehow I just felt a bit disappointed.  Maybe if it hadn't looked so nice it would have been better.

reviews.title: Tasty
reviews.text: Really awesome bubble tea here, best I've had. The coconut milk special is absolutely to die for...yum. :) Tons of menu options and friendly staff. For every bubble tea lover.

reviews.title: Yay YoYo!
reviews.text: This is exactly what Rotterdam was missing: delicious bubble tea. I don't think you can ever go wrong with any of the flavours, although the coconut milk is better than I've tasted anywhere else. Taro flavour also very nice. Unlike elsewhere the tapioca does not come with your tea as standard, which encourages you to try the boba or jelly.

reviews.title: Hangout in Rotterdam with a bubble tea
reviews.text: My all-time-favorite... Mango milk tea with tapioca bubbles!!! Delicious. Also hip and cozy atmosphere inside with lounge seats. Worth a visit. (Make sure they are not too mean with the amount of bubbles.)

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ family guide
tripContent.description: "Our family loves going to Orlando—and not just for the theme parks. Yes, we enjoy getting to ride rollercoasters and be transported to another world, but spending time in a colorful, diverse city and the surrounding nature is delightful. We live just over an hour from Orlando, so when we feel the need for good city vibes and to feel welcome in a neighborhood besides our own, Orlando is a fantastic option for us." - Rob Taylor, 2TravelDads.com

tripContent.title: Orlando: An LGBTQ+ guide for families
tripContent.description: "As a two-mom family who has been traveling to Orlando five to six times a year, we see the city like a second home. We absolutely love the theme parks but Orlando has so much more to offer! We love experiencing Orlando's rich diversity, fantastic food, incredible art and culture, plus a fun soccer game here and there. Join me, Allison Mertzman, as I share some of my family's favorite Orlando attractions with you!" - Allison Mertzman

seoInfo.metaDescription: We admit it: You can’t see everything London has to offer in just 48 hours. But with a strategic itinerary, you can get a surprisingly solid sense of England’s capital. From a taste of the royal life at Buckingham Palace to a taste of beer at a local pub, think of this as a London sampler.
